  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely slice (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>, <strong>sliced garlic </strong>and<strong> </strong>100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>thyme</strong> (chuck it in, stalks and all!) and cook, covered, for 8-10 min or until the onion has completely softened, stirring frequently</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>macaroni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the<strong> macaroni</strong> for 6-7 min or until cooked with a bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>macaroni</strong> reserving 150ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [200ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> and set aside until later, reserve the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has completely softened, add your <strong>Marmite</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Cook, uncovered, for 4-5 min further or until caramelised</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk and stir frequently to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once caramelised, discard the thyme stalks</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pot to a medium heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, then add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 100ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong> into the roux, and cook for 4-5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, then stir through <strong>half</strong> the <strong>grated cheese </strong>(save the rest for later!) with your<strong> clotted cream </strong>– this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add most of the <strong>caramelised onion</strong> to the cheese sauce with the <strong>drained macaroni </strong>and stir everything together – this is your <strong>mac 'n' cheese mixture</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>mac 'n' cheese mixture</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>and sprinkle over the<strong> remaining caramelised onion</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>remaining grated cheese</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for 10-12 min or until golden and bubbling – this is your <strong>French onion-style mac 'n' cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the mac 'n' cheese is cooking, combine your <strong>white wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>Dijon mustard </strong>with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>sugar </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and shred roughly</p><p>Add the <strong>shredded lettuce</strong> to the dressing<strong> </strong>and toss – this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/french-onion-style-mac-n-cheese/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>French onion-style mac 'n' cheese </strong>with the <strong>dressed</strong> <strong>salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
